From: ETA project local patch
Subject: [PATCH] Lockfree ObjectDB read for Callable::callp

Problem
-------
ObjectDB::get_instance (core/object/object.h:1106) acquires
`spin_lock.lock()` on every call. The lock guards add_instance /
remove_instance from the lookup, so writers (Object construction
and destruction) can't race a torn read of the slot validator.

Callable::callp (core/variant/callable.cpp:59) is on the dispatch
path for every signal emission and every deferred-call invocation.
Each call resolves the target ObjectID via ObjectDB::get_instance,
paying one spin_lock acquire/release pair.

On a 128-tick authoritative server, that's hundreds of atomic
lock/unlock pairs per physics tick (one per receiver per signal,
times all the signals fired in that tick). The lock is uncontended
in single-threaded game logic but the atomic ops still issue
memory fences and dirty cache lines.

Fix
---
1. Add a sibling ObjectDB::get_instance_unchecked() that skips
   the lock. Same _ALWAYS_INLINE_ body, just without the spin_lock
   pair around the validator check and slot read.

2. Make Callable::callp call the unchecked variant for the
   standard (non-custom) Callable path. That's the hot one — the
   custom path (CallableCustom*) never touches ObjectDB.

3. The unchecked variant is gated behind DEV_ASSERT(Thread::is_main_thread()).
   In DEV_ENABLED builds, any callp() invocation from a worker
   thread fires the assert and we know the safety assumption broke.
   Release and DEBUG builds skip the assertion and ship the lockfree
   path directly.

The unchecked variant is intentionally a separate function — the
locked get_instance stays for the many other callers that need
its safety. Only Callable::callp opts in.

Caveats
-------
- Resource loader workers can spawn Objects on worker threads. As
  long as those Objects never become the target of a Callable
  whose callp runs concurrently with their construction/destruction,
  we're safe. In practice the game's worker-spawned resources
  don't participate in signal dispatch from worker threads.
- If a DEV_ASSERT fires on Thread::is_main_thread(), switch the
  caller back to the locked get_instance() and audit the threading
  for that emission site.

